          <p class="ba-sub">For agencies that need deep technical site audits — every broken link, redirect chain, and duplicate tag across every client site.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Screaming Frog is the technical SEO audit standard. At $259/year (~$22/month) for unlimited crawls, it's the best value technical tool on this list. Desktop-based crawler that finds broken links, redirect chains, duplicate meta tags, missing alt text, canonical issues, thin content, and pagination problems across any client site. Agencies use it for new client audits, quarterly technical checks, and post-migration verification. The scheduled crawl feature automates recurring audits without manual intervention.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Unlimited crawls — audit every client site as often as needed for $22/mo total</h4><p>At $259/year for unlimited crawls, Screaming Frog has the best cost-per-audit of any technical tool. Run new client audits and quarterly checks without per-crawl fees.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Deepest technical audit output — the tool most senior SEOs use for critical audits</h4><p>Custom extraction via XPath, JavaScript rendering, log file analysis. For complex technical issues, nothing matches Screaming Frog's depth.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Scheduled crawls — automated recurring technical audits per client</h4><p>Set it and it runs. Flags new issues between manual checks so your team catches problems before clients notice them.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: desktop-only, no client reporting, steep learning curve</h4><p>Screaming Frog produces data — you turn it into a client report manually. Not a client-facing tool. Requires an experienced SEO to interpret output.</p></div></li>
