        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">DashThis is the more flexible alternative to AgencyAnalytics. Where AgencyAnalytics uses pre-built templates, DashThis lets you drag and drop any data widget into custom layouts. For agencies with very different client types — one client cares about organic traffic, another about local Map Pack, another about conversion rate — DashThis creates fully customized views per client without maintaining separate tools. Full white-label branding on all plans, including the $42/month entry tier that covers 3 dashboards.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Drag-and-drop dashboard builder — fully customizable per client type</h4><p>Each client gets a dashboard showing exactly the metrics they care about. No forcing a local business client into an SEO-heavy template they don't understand.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Full white-label on all plans — including the $42/month entry tier</h4><p>Unlike competitors that reserve white-label for higher plans, DashThis includes branding at the lowest tier.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Wide connector library — Google Analytics, Search Console, social, ads, and more</h4><p>Pulls data from every platform clients care about into one branded view. Comparable integration coverage to AgencyAnalytics.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: more setup time per client than AgencyAnalytics templates</h4><p>The flexibility that makes DashThis powerful also makes it slower to set up. For agencies onboarding 5+ clients per month, the manual configuration adds up.</p></div></li>
