        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#10 · $99+/MO · FULL-STACK AUTOMATION</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Search Atlas (OTTO) — Best for agencies wanting full-stack technical SEO automation</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For mid-size agencies managing 5+ client websites that need technical fixes, content, and local SEO in one system.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Search Atlas's OTTO SEO installs as a JavaScript tag on client sites. Once active, it auto-fixes meta tags, schema markup, broken links, canonicals, header optimization, alt text, and internal linking — without manual intervention. It generates content from topical maps, builds backlinks through digital PR, and manages Google Business Profile. The scope is unmatched: if you want one tool handling technical fixes, content, backlinks, and local SEO simultaneously, OTTO comes closest. The limitations are real though: documented GBP module bugs, platform stability issues reported on G2, and a real cost that stacks to $158–198/month per site when you add the OTTO add-on.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Broadest scope — technical SEO, content, backlinks, and local SEO in one platform</h4><p>No other tool on this list attempts to do all four simultaneously. For agencies wanting maximum consolidation, OTTO has the widest net.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>JavaScript-based technical fixes — deploys across any CMS without developer work</h4><p>Drop a tag on any client site and OTTO starts fixing technical issues automatically. No CMS access required beyond script installation.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Topical map content generation — systematic keyword cluster coverage per site</h4><p>OTTO builds topical authority maps and generates content systematically. More structured than most content tools.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: buggy GBP module, platform stability issues, and real cost of $158–198/site/mo</h4><p>The OTTO add-on ($59–99/site/mo) stacks on top of the base plan. For an agency with 10 clients, that's $1,580–1,980/month in OTTO add-ons alone. Plus base plan. The ROI math only works at high client margins.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
